  "build": {
    "buildCommand": "cd /Users/ggiak/www/esolutions.gr/planos\ngit add src/hook/roundtrip.mjs plugin/bin/planos tests/extract-plan-contract.test.mjs\ngit -c core.pager=cat diff --cached --stat\ngit commit --quiet -m \"fix(roundtrip): extractPlan accepts a bare authored Document (skill-contract)\n\nThe /planos-prd, /planos-plan, /planos-review skills document piping the\nBARE authored document JSON to bin/planos (e.g. planos-prd.md:348\n\\`echo '<json>' | node bin/planos prd\\`). But extractPlan only read\ntool_input.plan from the ExitPlanMode hook envelope, so a bare doc\nreturned '' → degradeToProse silently discarded the authored content.\nThis is the likely root of the original 'when the plan was done it\nfailed with an error' (the authored PRD came back empty/degraded).\nTests passed only because they feed the wrapped {tool_input:{plan}}.\n\nFix: if stdin parses to a planos Document (schemaVersion+type+blocks)\nand has no tool_input.plan, treat the raw text AS the plan. Pure shape\ncheck — no network/model/import (AC-17-safe; import-graph VERDICT\nCLEAN). tool_input.plan still takes precedence; non-document JSON still\nreturns '' (degrade path intact); non-JSON still returned verbatim.\n\n- tests/extract-plan-contract.test.mjs: NEW 6-case regression\n  (bare doc used / plan-type / wrapped envelope / precedence /\n  non-doc still '' / non-JSON verbatim).\n- plugin/bin/planos rebuilt (npm run build:bin) so the bundled CLI\n  carries the fix; bin-bundle drift gate green.\n\ne2e verified: bare JSON | bundled bin/planos export now preserves the\nauthored title. Full suite 35/35; tsc clean; AC-17 CLEAN.\"\ngit -c core.pager=cat log --oneline -7",
    "testCommand": "echo \"=== packaging.test.mjs ===\" && cat tests/packaging.test.mjs 2>/dev/null && echo \"\" && echo \"=== test runner / npm test ===\" && cat tests/run-all.mjs 2>/dev/null | head -60 ; echo \"---\" ; grep -rl \"ac17Roots\\|import-graph\\|bin/planos\" tests/ 2>/dev/null",
